sample_data/
data/inbox/
data/archive/

# в”Ђв”Ђ Inbox dedup ledger вЂ” INTENTIONALLY COMMITTED в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# data/processed_attachments.json is the SHA256 idempotency ledger for the
# Gmail attachment watcher. It MUST persist across GitHub Actions runs
# (ephemeral runners reset the filesystem every Monday), so we commit it.
# Contains only hashes, filenames, ISO timestamps, and Gmail message IDs вЂ”
# no PHI. The workflow's "Commit inbox ledger" step keeps it in sync.
# See INBOX_LEDGER_PERSISTENCE_DECISION.md for the rationale.
!data/processed_attachments.json
**/March */
**/Weekly Report*
**/Salon Summary*
**/Employee KPI*
**/FS Salon Dashboard*
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# в”Ђв”Ђ Weekly backfill report files вЂ” provided locally, NOT committed в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# Tony downloads 12 salons Г— ~52 weeks of POS reports into
# backfill/weekly/{Zenoti,SU}/<YYYY-MM-DD>/ folders. Bulk inputs (reproducible
# by re-download, carry stylist names) вЂ” keep the repo lean. The loader, the
# bucket dirs (.gitkeep), and READMEs ARE committed. See BACKFILL_RUNBOOK.md.
backfill/weekly/Zenoti/**
backfill/weekly/SU/**
!backfill/weekly/Zenoti/.gitkeep
!backfill/weekly/SU/.gitkeep
